# Code owners — who must approve changes to the project's instruction &
# guidance files before they can merge to `main`.
#
# Enforced by branch protection on `main`: "Require review from Code Owners"
# is on, so a pull request that changes any path below needs @benclink's
# approval to merge — on top of the normal review + passing CI checks.
#
# Note: GitHub does not let an author approve their own pull request. If you
# author a change to one of these files, a *second* code owner must approve it.
# Right now @benclink is the only owner, so add a co-owner (or a team) here if
# you want solo edits to these files to be merge-able without waiting on Ben.

# Agent / contributor instructions
/CLAUDE.md            @benclink
/docs/                @benclink

# The ownership file itself — so the lock can't be quietly removed in a PR.
/.github/CODEOWNERS   @benclink
